            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Hd1e108">Rubrica 4</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De adulatione: blandimento et assentione</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>¶ De adulatione blandimen
      <lb ed="#V" n="18" break="no"/>to et assentione. Rubrica. 4
      
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e121">
               <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>Alomon in prouerb. c.
      <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>i. <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e127">Si te lactaue
        <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>rint peccatores: ne quiescas eis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e133"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e135"> c.
        <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>27. Meliora sunt vulnera diligen
        <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>tis quam fraudientis oscula. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e144">
               <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e148">¶ Isocrates in exhortation. Odi blandientes
        <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>tanquam decipientes: nam vtrique commissarii fa
        <lb ed="#V" n="26" break="no"/>cti iniuriantur commissis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e156">
               <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e160">¶ Aristoteles retho. li. i. c. 20. Adulationem
        <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>recipere et adulatorem delectabile est: apparens
        <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>enim admirator est. Apparens amicus adu
        <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>lator est. / Li. 2 c. 9. Laudare presentem: adu
        <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>lationis est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e172"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e174"> Idem ethincorum libro 4. c. 4. Omnes
        <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>blanditores obfequiosi seruiles et humiles
        <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>sunt. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e182"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e184"> Li. 8. c. 5. Amatores adulationis mul
        <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>ti sunt. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e190"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e192"> Idem magnorum moralium li. i. c. 51
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>Adulator est plus decentibus et existentibus
        <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>adijciens. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e200">
               <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e204">¶ Terentius. i. comed scilicet n andria. ca. 3. Hoc
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>tempore obsequium amicos veritas odium parit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e211">
               <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e215">¶ Tullius retho. artis noue li. 5. c. 6. Habet
        <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>assentatio iocunda principia: eadem exitus
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>amarissimos affert. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e223">
               <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e227">¶ Ouidius sine titulo seu amorum liro i. c. 8. Im
        <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>pia sub dulci melle venena latent. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e233">
               <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e237">¶ Seneca epistolarum ad lucillum li. 6. e. 3. Adula
        <lb ed="#V" n="45" break="no"/>tio que similis est amicitie non imitatur tium <!--91.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>illam: sed vincit et preterit: aptis ac propitiis
        <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>auribus recipitur: ac in precordia ima descen
        <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>dit: eoipso gratiosa quo ledit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e254"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e256"> Idem in pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>uerb. Habet suum venenum blanda oratio. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e262">
               <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e266">¶ Auctor li. de formula honeste vite. ca. 4.
        <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>Adulatores deuita. Difficillimum continentie
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>opus est assentationes adulantium repellere
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>quorum sermones animum quadam voluptate re
        <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>soluunt. Nullius per assentatione amici
        <lb ed="#V" n="55" break="no"/>tiam merearis: nec hanc promerendi a te adi
        <lb ed="#V" n="56" break="no"/>tum aliis pandas. Non acerba sed blanda
        <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>verba timebis. Cunctis esto benignus: ne
        <lb ed="#V" n="58" break="no"/>mini blandus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e287">
               <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e291">¶ Cato. c. 2. Noli homines blandos: nimium
        <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>sermone probare. Fistula dulce canit vo
        <lb ed="#V" n="61" break="no"/>lucrem: dum decipit auceps. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e300"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e302"> c. 8. Sermo
        <lb ed="#V" n="62" break="no"/>nes blandos blesosque vitare memento.
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>Simplicitas veri fama est: fraus ficta loquendi </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e310">
               <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e314">¶ Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 12. et fi. e. 10. Graui
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>us percutit: qui blandiendo crassatur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e320"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e322"> Idem
        <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>de anima. c. 16. et antepenul. hostis dulcis ami
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>cus amarus est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e330">
               <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e334">¶ Uersificator fabularum esopi. 64. fab. et fi.
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>Blanditie plusquam dira venena nocent. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e340">
               <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e344">¶ Montenarius in luna cleri. c. 128. et pe.
        <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>Sugit adulator lac pectoris ad vber. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-d1e350">
               <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d24815-Qd1e354">¶ Prouerb. vulgar: Losenge de enemigo e
        <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>como passare a panigo. </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
